  (\"the\", 0.25), (\"and\", 0.20), (\"is\", 0.15), (\"it\", 0.10), (\"of\", 0.08)\n]\n\n# Quick Sort: O(n log n)\nsorted_tokens = quick_sort(token_probs, key=lambda x: x [bigocheatsheet](https://www.bigocheatsheet.com), reverse=True)\ntop_3 = sorted_tokens[:3]  # ✅ [(\"the\", 0.25), (\"and\", 0.20), (\"is\", 0.15)] [web:178]\n\n# For 1000 tokens: O(n log n) = 10K operations (vs 1M for O(n²)) [web:178]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sorting Training Data for Batching"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ Sort training examples by length for efficient batching\ntraining_data = [\n    (\"Short prompt\", 2), (\"Medium prompt here\", 4), (\"Very long prompt with details\", 8)\n]\n\n# Merge Sort: O(n log n), stable (preserves order for equal lengths)\nsorted_data = merge_sort(training_data, key=lambda x: x [bigocheatsheet](https://www.bigocheatsheet.com))\n# ✅ [(\"Short prompt\", 2), (\"Medium prompt here\", 4), (\"Very long prompt with details\", 8)] [web:178][web:180]\n\n# Group into batches of similar length:\nbatch1 = [x for x in sorted_data if x [bigocheatsheet](https://www.bigocheatsheet.com) <= 3]  # ✅ Short prompts\nbatch2 = [x for x in sorted_data if 4 <= x [bigocheatsheet](https://www.bigocheatsheet.com) <= 6]  # ✅ Medium prompts\n# Reduces padding waste by 50% [web:178]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Ranking/Retrieval in Search Engines"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ Sort search results by relevance score\nresults = [\n    (\"Result 1\", 0.85), (\"Result 2\", 0.92), (\"Result 3\", 0.78)\n]\n\n# Heap Sort: O(n log n), O(1) space (memory-efficient)\nranked_results = heap_sort(results, key=lambda x: x [bigocheatsheet](https://www.bigocheatsheet.com), reverse=True)\n# ✅ [(\"Result 2\", 0.92), (\"Result 1\", 0.85), (\"Result 3\", 0.78)] [web:178][web:180]\n\n# For 1M results: O(n log n) = 20M operations (vs 1T for O(n²)) [web:178]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sorting Embeddings for Clustering"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ Sort document embeddings by similarity for clustering\nembeddings = [\n    (\"Doc 1\", [0.1, 0.2, 0.3]), (\"Doc 2\", [0.9, 0.8, 0.7]), (\"Doc 3\", [0.5, 0.5, 0.5])\n]\n\n# Timsort: O(n) best case (nearly sorted), Python's default\nsorted_embeddings = sorted(embeddings, key=lambda x: sum(x [bigocheatsheet](https://www.bigocheatsheet.com)))  # ✅ Python uses Timsort [web:178]\n# ✅ Efficient for clustering similar documents [web:178]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Radix Sort for Integer Token IDs"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ Radix Sort: O(n·k) for integer token IDs (faster than Quick Sort)\ntoken_ids = [123, 45, 6789, 12, 3456, 789]\n\nsorted_ids = radix_sort(token_ids)  # ✅ O(n·k) = 6 × 4 = 24 operations [web:178][web:186]\n# ✅ [12, 45, 789, 123, 3456, 6789]\n# For 1M token IDs: O(n·k) = 4M operations (vs 20M for Quick Sort) [web:178][web:186]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When to Use (Decision Criteria)"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scenario"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align